HEADWORD: Gymnasiarch
<hw>Gym*na"si*arch</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧m*n⟦amac⟧"z⟦icr⟧*⟦aum⟧rk)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>gymnasiarchus</ets>, Gr.
<grk>gymnasi`archos</grk>; <grk>gymna`sion</grk> + <grk>'a`rchein</grk>
to govern: cf. F. <ets>gymnasiarque</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Gr.
Antiq.)</fld> <def>An Athenian officer who superintended the gymnasia,
